<-
	Everything BELOW "<-" mark is IGNORED.
	Everything ABOVE "<-" mark must be in the form of "LinuxDev=AbiDev".
	Both Device Numbers are hexadecimal "MMMmmmmm",
where	"mmmmm" - is the Minor Device Number (low 20 bits),
and	"MMM" - is the Major Device Number (high 12 bits). 
	Empty Lines and Comments are not allowed !

	Example - map "/dev/mapper/VolGroup00-LogVol00" (major 253, minor 0)
	to "/dev/hda2" (major 3, minor 2):
0FD00000=00300002
